1. pandas needs g++
: sudo apt-get install g++

2. scipy needs LAPACK/BLAS pkg:
: sudo apt-get install gfortran libopenblas-dev liblapack-dev

3. If a command not found while the file exists on ubuntu (x86_64), it is because the file is 32-bit binary
: sudo apt-get install ia32-libs # UBUNTU
: yum install glibc.i686 # CENTOS

4. GUI editor needs Tkinterp in Python
: $ apt-get install python-tk in debian linux
: $ yum install tkinter in red hat linux

5. To install matplotlib, installed freetype-devel and libpng-devel
